<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="278" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1436,1401,2002]" pageId="23" pageNumber="278">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1401,1426]" pageId="23" pageNumber="278">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Distinguished among species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Odontorhagus" authorityName="Odontorhagus" box="[664,986,1401,1426]" class="Insecta" family="Schizopteridae" genus="Schizoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="278" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[664,796,1401,1425]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="278">Schizoptera</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[816,977,1401,1425]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="278">Odontorhagus</emphasis>
)
</taxonomicName>
by the broadly ovoid body shape, the prominent fuscous patch covering more than 1/2 of the wing membrane, and the thin, tomahawk-shaped process of the subgenital plate.
</paragraph>
