<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="278" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1436,1401,2002]" pageId="23" pageNumber="278">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,1905,1930]" pageId="23" pageNumber="278">Discussion.</emphasis>
No specimens examined matched the description of this species, ventral images of the 
<typeStatus box="[1338,1436,1905,1930]" pageId="23" pageNumber="278">holotype</typeStatus>
are available, but the pointmout obscures the process of the subgenital plate; therefore our re-description is solely somatic. For an illustration of the subgenital plate of this species see 
<bibRefCitation author="McAtee" box="[923,1243,1977,2002]" pageId="23" pageNumber="278" refString="McAtee, W. L., &amp; Malloch, J. R. (1925) Revision of bugs of the family Cryptostemmatidae in the collection of the United States National Museum. Proceedings of the United States National Museum, 67 (13), 1 - 42." type="journal article" year="1925">McAtee and Malloch (1925)</bibRefCitation>
Figure 61.
</paragraph>
